caption: Great food
Portions are big, food was delicious. Highly recommend.

Love their pho gain! Good service and awesome food. It's a very small restaurant and you will wait awhile if it gets busy, but it's worth it. The prices are reasonable. The pho is great on a cold day .
thai food, yeah, delicious. Service is always awesome even when they have a full house. I've had nothing but pleasant experiences here and plan to keep coming back. This place has a good design.
thai food... my favorite treat. i often meet people here to talk. looking forward to going back again. the prices are good for what you get. makes me feel like i in nashville again.
Good place for tasty Thai food. Entered near nine, it wasn't busy. I will probably become a regular. Menu is similar to a restaurant in Jacksonville I liked.
IMO, probably the best place for Thai food in the Loop. Great classic thai dishes like pad thai, pad see ew, massaman curry, etc.

Good Thai dining experience. Have been patronizing for years even before name and ownership change. My favorite chicken Rama. If you enjoy rice, order extra as servings with entree are usually sparse. Maybe business model should be adjusted. Pleasing decor. Paid parking across the street from restaurant.
Excellent food, welcoming staff members, always excellent mood. They charge fair pricing and the food quality is great. Highly recommended.
Awesome variety of foods, nice place and the staffs are very friendly.
Great Thai food! Highly recommend the beef fried rice and the pad kee mao.

This was a postive experience. My friend and I had the place to ourselves and had 5 star service from our waiter.  The sushi was delicious and fresh. The menu is bigger than you might imagine.  You know this place is good if the water was BOMB! New sushi spot!!!!

I would not willing eat this food again. My husband completely agrees. It's perfectly normal to occasionally encounter small pieces of herbal components in Thai food, but there were very large inedible chunks of lemongrass, roots, and other unidentifiable woody things. Where was the ginger? I don't know. They used lemons instead of limes which contributed to what I can only describe as an overall unpleasant flavor profile that was present in every dish. Very disappointing.

This site is my first choice place.  Of all restaurants I know I favor it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to this restaurant. everytime  I I need a proper dinner, this place comes straight to my head. very good and varied  food and a rich cuisine.courteous team, and nice vibes. Not less important, the pay is affordable. I tell about this place with great pleasure.

Love the food here, my favorite being the pineapple fried rice which has shrimp and chicken. They cut a pineapple in half and then serve the food in it.  Even the pick up service is good and they do follow any additional instructions

The Massaman curry was very nice. The chicken had a great texture and flavor, and the curry itself had a delicious, toasted peanut flavor. My only complaint is it could have been spicier! I ordered it extra hot, maybe I'll try extra extra hot next time?
I really love the dishes and customer service, awesome area  to my apartment. The workers are always super friendly. Will come back again.
Delicious food, I got the Spicy chicken curry and the Spider roll. Food was delivered within 30 mins
I simply like their dishes. I always get awesome customer service here. The place is always clean and the staff members are always friendly. Keep up the good work.
Awesome 👏🏻
Unpretentious atmosphere and yummy good Thai food.
Good thai food, vegan friendly!
Stay away. So many things wrong with this profit hungry restaurant
I've ordered like a dozen of their items and they're all so good. My favorite is the pad see ewe. I could eat here every day tbh🔥💯
Awesome thai
This place simply knows how to treat their customers. Regularly with a super friendly attitude. The food is fairly priced, regularly delicious and neat.
The menu and service were above our expectations. I really loved the ambience of this spot. Excellent spot to take the family out for dinner.
The food is regularly fresh and yummy, cashiers gives good service. I like how clean it is and ambience. I highly recommend this spot.
The service was extremely pushy but the food was excellent so take your pick.
Amazing food!!! Definitely go by what they recommend 😃
Great place, very tasty food
Fantastic and delightful food, I loved the atmosphere the place has, and the employees were kind. I will surely visit here next time.
I am always pleased when I stop by for lunch!

Inventive Thai restaurant with an Asian fusion menu, including sushi, with very nice ambience in the South Loop. Usually not crowded, which is a super benefit when you can't get into better-known restaurants. Prices are also reasonable; we paid $200 for a party of 6, with some people drinking alcohol.
Excellent food, good price
Excellent service, but the food is a little sweet to us.

We met with friends at this place for lunch. This spot was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, we were not disappointed. The crew welcomed us with a smile and we felt good. The food was just great. We loved this restaurant a lot and we shall absolutely come back again. Highly recommended.

Menu is pretty long. I had the pad thai, which was decent, but a tad too sweet. One of my friends had the chicken curry, and he said it was pretty good. The ambience is pretty casual. Also could be a good place to bring your special someone, if they are into thai cuisine.

Although the staff are very competent, the menu items are well chosen and the decor is quite pleasant the incredibly heavy use of salt ruined the meal.  My Korean dinner companion, who is well accustomed to fairly salty food, was also unhappy.  The soups were the worst.  They were salted to the point that the taste of lemongrass and ginger were obliterated. The entrees were similarly heavily salted, blotting out all other flavours .  My co-workers have commented on this point, but I thought I would try it out anyway.  Sadly, not going back.
Decent thai restaurant.

I take my family to this nice place often! This is my favorite place to eat.  I go there frequently. The food is excellent, the staff is professional and the prices are affordable. I enjoy being in this spot for a nice lunch.
Multiple health code violations.
Good food and prices aren't outrageous. Sapparo on tap is really good

This site is my preferable place.  Of all restaurants I know I prefere it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to visit this restaurant. when  I feel like having a proper dinner, this is the place that comes first to my head. very good and many types of  food and a rich menu.well mannered staff members, and nice ambience. Not less important, the cost is affordable. I sent my friends to this restaurant with no doubt.
Every bite was delicious and the service was wonderful. We all had something different and everyone was pleased with their choices. Thank Amarit Thai for a lovely evening.
Very delightful place food is very good and the service is very
The food was excellent and the staff were very attentive and pleasant.
Great place! The staff were very friendly and the food was fantastic

I walk in and it seems pretty busy, however  I was seated immediately and given a menu, a glass of water, and plenty of time to sort through my menu indecisiveness. I got the ginger chicken which was delicious with bold ginger and onion flavor with punches of pepper. To end my meal, I got the iced Thai bubble tea, which was a beautiful drink that felt almost like having thai tea flavored ice cream with pops of the tapioca spheres. The wait staff were super attentive despite a busy Saturday.
Chicken very dry even though it was in soup.
The place offers a large variety of delicious food. I liked eating here. Staff members are always very kind, pricing is convenient and the spot is always clean.
Amazing no wait on a Wednesday afternoon and it’s SOOOOO YUMMY !!!!! Well worth the traffic to come here ! 10 stars

This place seems to be most popular with a work/lunch crowd. It's tastefully arranged and not too loud or crowded. The service is exceptionally attentive and there's quite a broad variety of choices. I prefer spicy Thai, and have found they will adjust the heat levels upon request.

Good "Thai" food. The four of us had a variety of dishes: spicy beef (watch the chili sauce as it builds) which was tender and flavorful; tom yum soup which was flavorful and NOT sweet; lemon grass seafood soup (decent price peformance, all seafood was good); ginger chicken (much too sweet and good flavors); and tasty mild yellow curry; with all three flavors of ice cream (really quite good). Price was excellent for Chicago for such food.
Good food, good service, good prices.

Great service, prices, offers gluten free pad thai but MOST important, twas open at 4.00pm on a friday. What really annoys me about certain cities that ‘think’ they are global but are really small towns is limited food options at 4.00pm or 11.00pm. Chicago falls into this category. My hotel ( Blake) recommended 5 places but they were all closed!! I found Amarit by accident. Apologies for the rant.. I’m still sensitive about once being kicked out of a spanish tapas restaurant at 10.30pm on a friday night in chicago. Big City Ron
Nice food

I wish I could give it zero stars. The food tasted rushed and the chicken was somewhat spoiled. I barely touched my food. The service was even worst. A server didn’t come by for quite some time after we sat down with hardly any other customers in the restaurant. Seems like they were more concerned with the to go orders rather than their physical customers. When I asked if I could split the ice cream half and half, the guy waiter asked the lady (must have been the manger) and she quickly responded NO with a harsh attitude. Then to top it all off, she came by the table (they never came by once during our meal and asked if everything was ok) and scolded my boyfriend for leaving less than a 10% tip. If it were up to me I would have left nothing! One of the worst restaurants and experience in the south loop. There’s no wonder this place was empty!
Food isn't fresh, musty indoors
A favorite family place!
Good food with generous portions and great service. The Thai tea smoothie was delicious.
Fair prices for good meals
The food is always fresh and tasty, employees hands over great customer service. I really like how clean it is and mood. I highly recommend this spot.

Not authentic at all. The Kao Soy (Northern Thai Curry) had zero spice, the noodles were undercooked, & the chicken dry. It did not include the side additions this dish traditionally comes with. They didn’t even have lime...?! Not worth it, don’t recommend.
Lousy service

This restaurant is well organized and artistically modern.  The environment is calming and the employees from my experience are well trained, kind and respectful.  I rarely eat sushi but when I do I always feel satisfied, so I decided to order the “Crunchy Spicy Tuna Roll” and it was good as expected.  I recommend Amarit Thai and Sushi to city locals and travelers.

I ordered the Tom Kha Kai Soup via Uber Eats. I have had this soup more than twenty times from Thai restaurants and this was the worst yet because it was very very bland and came with very little veggies and chicken. After spending $26 on lunch delivery, I won't be ordering this again unfortunately.
They close at 9:30 and very rude service
The employees are rude and the restaurant is dirty. Do you still want to eat here? With so many good food options in Chicago, there's no need to waste your time and money dining at Amarit.
Excellent location for delicious thai food. It was so fresh. The staff was very welcoming and observant. The bill was appropriate.
I love Thai food and Amarit doesn't disappoint. All the classic dishes and drinks to go with them. Friendly staff and charming atmosphere.

Let me start off by saying I am obsessed with peanut sauce. I always order the same things from Thai restaurants to get an idea of the quality of food I'm in store for and that's a chicken pad thai with peanut sauce, chicken satay (and peanut sauce), and/or spring rolls. Amarit checks all the boxes and has some of the best flavoring from most places I've tried! This is always a great walkable lunch spot to grab food to go for me when I'm working downtown. I haven't had the pleasure of sitting down to eat, but the atmosphere during my visits has always seemed professional and comfortable. Don't skip by this place, enjoy a bite!
Delicious food, reasonable prices and huge portions! Pictured: spring rolls, pineapple fried rice ( no egg or onion ) and Singapore Curry Noodles

Been here three or four times and the first time the food was great but I left thinking the restaurant itself was dirty.  Gone back four or five times and it's still just as dirty but the food is not good at all.  Wanted to like this place but I just can't bring myself to.
Very nice service and tasty food. I only tried the Thai food.
Real tasty. Fast service. Fair prices!!!

I've been working in the area for 5 years and consistently pick this for lunch. I've never had anything bad off of the noodle or entree menu.  My favorites are pineapple friend rice, pad see ew, and pepper steak. They are all large portions for a good price. The servers are fast and attentive. I've had the sushi a few times and is also really good.
Great food, good drinks, and friendly service.
Delicious.....
Sushi and rice was great

I’m not a true adventurous eater so when my wife first suggested to order from this place. I said ok let’s try it out. Years have past and a review overdue. The pad khee mao is my go to as my wife always order chicken & veggies. First time ordering pad khee mao I asked for spicy plus added their hit sauce and my tongue nearly fell off. LOL To make a long story short I recommend this place. I like ordering out because I have small kids now and it’s lots of work to keep them seated.
Plus in this restaurant are not only that food are exquisite,luscious,and delicious, but also the interior ornament are unique,elegant,and its impressive style.
,Really nice atmosphere, nice Asian style food,helpful staff
Excellent food and.service... order the Pineapple fried rice with shrimp and chicken! Pretty affordable too!!!! Loved it!!!😋😋

I placed an order through Rival for Amarit Thai. I got the Crunchy Gomae Roll and Veggie Egg Rolls. The pickup was great. I didn't really get to interact with the staff much, but I loved how quickly they moved when I walked in. The presentation for this carryout order was on a whole. Different. Level. It was beautiful! Honestly, though, the taste was only ok. I'd possibly return again on a very hungry day.
Food & service were excellent.
Love the kao soi and mango sticky rice. Tastes like I had in Chiang Mai.
(Translated by Google) Very delicious  (Original) Muy riquísimo

Delicious squash curry. Big portions appropriate for the price. Restaurant was a bit loud but it was crowded. The staff were attentive and the good came out quickly. It was a great experience just wished I lived close by to eat there more often.

(Translated by Google) It is a restaurant with very delicious food I had the privilege of working with all those people who collaborate in that restaurant very very friendly delicious everything.  (Original) Es un restaurante con comida muy deliciosa yo tuve el privilegio de trabajar con todas esas personas q  colaboran en ese restaurante muy muy amables delicioso todo.
Just wonderful food from beginning to end. Nice staff. Close enough to theaters and shopping to walk there.
A favorite place for delicious thai food. i love this place, excellent food & service. the service was very helpful and observant. the place has an awesome atmosphere.
Great food and friendly staff. Have been going there for years. You should definitely try it.
Food was great. Service was great. Atmosphere was chill & calm.
Very bad service very bad food
We were looking for Thai food near our hotel and this fit the bill. Loved my curry but my daughter was not too fond if the Thai ice tea (which was more like a smoothie). I LOVED it.
A great little hidden Thai gem in the heart of downtown Chicago.

One of my favorite spots in south loop. I usually get the rice soup, pad knee mao or pad kra pao (basil and chicken). My friend had tuna tataki, it was quite yummy. I like the variety of their food options. The entrance has not 100% perfect ramp, hard for some wheelchair users to navigate though.
Good Pad Thai
i would recommend somewhere else for Thai cuisine. Tried Pad Thai and Duck Curry. Disappointed by the food quality and taste.

Chicken Pad Thai is my favorite however here it was awful. After being served, the waitress never came and asked how things tasted. I had to flag her down to ask if there was some sauce or something I could put on it as it was very dry.  She told me yes but it would cost $3 for peanut sauce. I asked her if I could have the sauce they put on the Pad Thai and was told I could only order extra peanut sauce. So I told her ok as it didn't taste good the way it was. She then gave me a bad tasting peanut sauce. They could see I didn't eat any of it but didn't care. This was the worst Thai place I have ever eaten at and the worst service I have ever received. I would never recommend this restaurant.
Pretty good to adequate Thai. Lovely setting, great service.

Great dinner for 5. We enjoyed our dinner immensely. We had the chicken satay, pot stickers, shrimp wonton and chicken noodle soups for appetizers and they were all good.   For mains we had chicken fried rice, Amarit special and a couple sushi rolls. Again every thing was prepared well. Service was attentive and friendly. We all enjoyed our meal.
My go to restaurant anytime any day 😁
Nice atmosphere and good service but the crab entree was mostly rice.
Godzilla Sushi was good combo of textures and flavors. Great venue for quiet Sunday outing, not crowded at all.
Great Thai spot for a quiet business lunch.  One of the few loop locations with Japanese curry on the menu!
One very stale Spring Roll sliced into dried-out tasteless bits? Really? $6 too.
good food :)
Food is not that good. They use too much lemon, and the pad thai was weak. Better places in chicago, don't waste your time.
Very nice place to dine for dishes prepared extremely well.  Definitely a repeat visit
Possibly the worst Pad Thai I've ever had and the sushi was not fresh. Totally disappointing.
Good food, good with kids.
Wonderful and attentive service, great food and value.

The staff was very friendly and the food was quick and tasty. A lovely atmosphere for a date and the staff doesn't linger, but is always around when you need something so perfect service. And the location is nice, right in the middle of the loop so I don't have to go out of my way to go there. We'll be going again!
Nice atmosphere! Tasty food
(Translated by Google) Pad khe want  (Original) Pad khe mau
Food was not exceptional. Comfortable seating. Diverse menu. Helpful staff.

(Translated by Google) Very great authentic Thai restaurant. We were here on recommendation. More than worth it.  (Original) Sehr tolles authentisches Thailokal. Wir waren auf Empfehlung hier. Hat sich mehr als gelohnt.
Great food, great portions. Priced reasonably. Highly recommended!
Tasty food, nice ambiance priced affordably
Good Thai food with great service.
Great place! Good food for a great value—such fun!
Pad Thai was okay. U don't think they cleaned out the shrimp ( where the organs and guts and poop are)
Sleek and intimate. Reasonably priced cuisine.
Decent place for lunch in the loop, good service.  tasty.
Good Thai restaurant in chicago downtown loop area!
Great food and service!
Good service but, the food didn't taste fresh. I didn't enjoy the food. Good prices especially for Downtown, Chicago.

Absolutely terrible. Ordered on Grubhub and got the wrong dish. When I called to let them know they said there was nothing they could do and refused to refund or send the correct food. Service is awful and unprofessional.

Absolute garbage service.  I ordered a dish I frequently get from grub hub.  They delivered it incorrectly.  I contacted the restaurant and they told it me they would give me a new dish that was properly prepared, they refused to give a refund, and then proceeded it wasn’t my fault for not specifying what I wanted.  Mind you this was a dish that I have ordered many times and every time it was the same correct order.  The arrogance of management is leading me to never going to this place again.

I do not care ABOUT what other people have said,  but the service was AMAZING. They are very friendly, the food tastes excellent as well the prices are affordable. Would recommend to anyone just visiting or living here in the beautiful city of Chicago.

Service was terrible and food was just ok. Had shrimp pad Thai. It was way too sweet. Shrimp fried rice was nice. Our server was incredibly rude and dismissive to my guest who had an accent. Apparently because of my guest's accent, the server refused to talk to her directly. My guest also paid but the server brought the card back to me. If you have to go here, get the good to go.

Great little Thai restaurant right around the corner.  I had the Tham Ka Ghai Soup (Coconut and Chicken) and my wife had the Ramen.  Both were excellent after a long walk around the city. Staff was very friendly; going to go back and get the Pineapple Fried Rice next time.

You wouldn't think their sushi would be fantastic but it is. We have had tons of sushi places and their signature rolls are unique enough and well executed. We have had a few other dishes from them but they did not wow us like the sushi. With a coupon their sushi is one of the best values in the city
Decent Asian food, not the best

Dynamite Roll was awful and smelled and looked like a can of tuna catfood was placed on top of it (see photo). I guess fresh sliced tuna isn't available here? Ive never seen shredded tuna on sushi before, probably for a reason. Ordered egg rolls, received all veggies and nothing else. Beef pad thai wasn't good and had mostly tofu and hardly any beef, and chicken fried rice was really dry. There are too many other options than to eat here.
Not bad and always tables available!
This restaurant has changed over time. The taste of the food has changed. The food doesn't have the flavor that is expected when eating Thai food.
perfect service and delicious food

My wife and I shared a Kao soi and ordered the mango sticky rice for dessert. I’m from Alabama but she was born in Thai so whenever we go to a big city she likes to take me to Thai restaurants, and I have to say this is one of the best and authentic we’ve been to. The lunch traffic is very low, so I’d recommend to go for lunch. Great experience and food, you can tell they take pride in their work. Highly recommend
Really nice place on a Sunday evening. Nice service all the time. Tasty food and Thai beer.
Good food, service and prices.
Great food and decent prices. Pictured is the Tom Yum soup and Shrimp Blanket appetizers
Pretty decent food and prices. Clean place.  Must-tries: - Pineapple Fried Rice - Pad See Eiw - Stir-fried Crispy Pork Belly with Rice
We had 6 Very good sushi rolls.
Rama chicken was excellent.
Really good thai taste.
Food is okay, but there isn't much Thai food in the area.

The food is definitely of Asian flavor, taste and look however I wouldn't call it strictly Thai only Asian cuisine. Service is fast, food tastes great, and is not greasy but well cooked and isn't overflown with gravy. The interior design is rather ascetic. It is worth trying.
Veggie pad thai. YUM.
First time visit but really impressed with the thai. I'll try sushi on my next visit
Food was amazing but i had the baddest service ever..
I'm not really into Thai food.  Was. With another couple that wanted to dine here.
Good food in a very authentic atmosphere. Reasonable prices for a local restaurant. Good food
Great Thai food!
It was a slow night, and my family had a wonderful meal. Very attentive staff. Four entrees, and four winners! Great prices for the quality.
I tried soups and appetizers here. Loved it.
Great food and Sushi. Reasonable prices. Great service.
The Thai was average and the ambiance was okay.  I had the cashew nut in brown sauce.
Great food and great price
Really good. Service is ok.
This place is one of the places that I go if I want some Thai food 🥘 - note that it may not be authentic to some people, they do have solid dishes to fill up your system. Highly recommend!
Average food and service is lacking - Opart Thai is so much better
Great food, clean dining room. Wood floors
If you are looking for authentic Thai food don't come here. It is okay for American Thai food. Will not come back.
Really enjoyed the coconut curry!
Delicious vegeterian thai food 🥘
Average attempt on Thai cuisine. It was convenient while I lived in the south loop but wouldn't really choose to go there once I have moved out of the area.
Everything was delicious!
Was introduced to Pad Thai in this place and fell in love ever since. Exceptionally affordable and tasty place to go!

Food was great but it was a little pricey for the sushi. Seems to be $1-2 more than most other places of similar quality. Definitely recommend but probably won't supplant our regular place (Kai Sushi) due to the price.
Ginger lime sole - delicious!  Chicken in noodle soup was.  A bit overcooked/dry.  Crab regions great, but the best was sticky rice with mango for dessert.
Sashimi too thin for the price. Curry mostly bamboo, taste also not good. Will not return.
Reliably good food

I asked for an off-menu dish that I really love and they happily obliged! There was only one server working the busy restaurant but he kept up pretty well. My friend's sesame chicken wasn't great, but the (secret) khao soi is pretty decent.
Good good with good portions and a large menu. Surprisingly not busy on a Saturday evening
Decent Thai food, convenient location
Got the crispy pork belly with chinese broccoli. It was delicious.
The duck curry was phenomenal
I went here to try out the food. Got to the door at 10:05pm. There were people inside dining. I was shewed away and a waitress said they closed at 10pm when clearly the sign on the door said 11pm.
One of my favorite sushi places in the South Loop!
Best egg rolls for vegetarians. Great option for lunch and dinner. Best Thai food I've had.
Everything we ordered did not disappoint - beef fried rice, chicken pad thai, pad see ewe and panang curry.
I paid $10.50 for a Singapore noodle. It had two things of shrimp and what looks like ramen noodles...disappointing to say the least
Sadly mediocre pad Thai. The tofu was especially bad and the chicken was bland. The mango sticky rice was good.

Food was extremely disappointing - pad thai was just noodles with tofu - no vegetables, little flavor, not authentic Thai at all. Very skimpy and cheap on ingredients. They also said they could make the food gluten free which is not the case as it has made me extremely sick. Coeliacs disease is extremely serious - not just a fad. If you can't do it gluten free - say you can't, don't just feed people stuff which will end up killing them!
Great food and even better prices. Definitely recommend to anyone that loves Oriental food.
Good service on a Sunday night. Patient to explain the dishes. Real thai people !

Good, local Thai spot. The portions are huge, especially on the pad Thai, and will leave you with lots of leftovers. Take out is just as good as dining in, and always tastes fresh. Tom yum soup is amazing!
Great neighborhood spot/nice and easy take out. Cant go wrong with the pad thai, tom yum soup and gyoza. Also love the bubble tea in honeydew. Stingy on soy sauce on to go orders though!

I live in the neighborhood.  Amarit is one of my favorite place to order from when I do not have time to cook.  The Pad Thai is OK and is served in generous portion.  The hot fried curry chicken is one of my favorite (the Gyoza too is really good).
Nothing special, nicer atmosphere than My Thai, but the food is very average. Spring rolls appeared to be drenched in pancake syrup, far too sweet.
The service was very good!!! I just give 4 stars because food a bit not worth for the price but overall is good.

Just came here for a conference and tried to find Thai food close to the hotel. I love it! I'm Thai and craving for spicy food all the times. They make great Tom Yum soup (I told them make it spicy and flavorful and I got beyond my expectation). I usually stereotype Thai restaurants here that they always Americanize Thai food. This place has kicked my assumption away.

Amarit is a solid restaurant - cool if you just want a quick Asian meal, but I wouldn't say that it's culinary greatness. I usually get the same thing every time - Mongolian Chicken, Veggie Egg Rolls, Brown Rice, and Steamed Veggies. The yellow curry chicken is tasty as well. They are very fast at processing your order. The restaurant is pretty big, but all the seats usually aren't filled. Good solid food if you are looking for quick Thai.
Excellent pot stickers, but pad thai was blah.
Very tasty. Fresh ingredients. Well prepared food.
mango sticky rice is to die for. great customer service, great food.  curry is top notch also
If you love Thai and Pan-Asian food, you will love this food. They are quick and service is with a smile. Very good dish selections. Variety of alcoholic drinks.

I reside in the neighborhood, one of my frequent favs. Always kind and usually knows what I will order before I speak. Super cool. I'm a fan of the sesame chicken with brown rice. (2) fried rice with peas, carrots and grilled chicken.
Nothing great but ok.
Good thai food

Good place. The staff was nice, I even overheard one of the servers recall what a regular customer usually orders.  The customer was impressed! Pad Thai was average and I don't particularly care for the large chunks of Tofu they put in it. However, after adding the table's chili sauce, the dish was a solid choice.
good place for a Thai fix. nothing fancy but food hasn't disappointed. love the pad thai and cashew chicken. spring rolls and crab rangoon is also yummy
Nice folks here, but the pad thai tops out at average. Good in a pinch or if you're wasted. They'll have your food ready ridiculously quickly.
